  "text": "The measurement and reduction of urgency symptoms is highly important because urgency is the central system and driver of all OAB symptoms. [CITATION_1] Although combination therapy has clear benefits for patients, the pathophysiology of OAB is multifaceted, with common symptoms such as urgency being mediated by both myogenic and neurogenic mechanisms. 16 Hence, combination therapy may not be completely successful in reducing symptoms as the full spectrum of pathophysiological pathways behind the clinical syndrome are not being addressed.",
